history.content:
CS170 + CS162 + CS186

The above will give you a solid foundation for interviews both algorithmic, technical, and system design questions. 

I have heard that CS161 is also really good to take so that you don't cause a data breach and know how to at least think about security when coding.

If you are interested in ML/AI CS189 is something you should add to your must takes.

Finally I will say that for interviews the Intro to Algorithmic DeCal (Leetcode 101) is great to take while recruiting. CS170 goes into a greater set of topics with far more depth but at the end of the day most companies will ask you to do some linked list or binary tree bs.

I know this has been asked before but I’m looking for answers from people who are/were in the industry. 
Which upper division courses have you found most relevant for both interviews and in your daily work as a software engineer?
